message.content: The theorem states that for any function from $\mathbb{R}$ to $\mathbb{R}$ and any real number $a$, the limit of the function $t \mapsto e^{-t} \int_a^t \frac{e^x - e^y}{x - y} \, dx \, dy$ as $t$ approaches infinity is $0$.
